CSS Advanced Project
üìñ Project Overview

This project builds upon the HTML, advanced project by focusing on styling using CSS.
The goal is to replicate the provided Figma design as closely as possible, applying CSS concepts such as selectors, classes, box properties, and responsive layout.

You will progressively style sections of the website including the header, banner, quotes, videos, membership, FAQ, and footer.

üéØ Learning Objectives

By the end of this project, you should be able to:

Understand what CSS is and how it works with HTML.

Add styles to elements using selectors, classes, and IDs.

Compute and apply CSS specificity values correctly.

Work with box model properties (margin, padding, border, width, height).

Understand how a browser loads and renders a webpage.

Apply clean and maintainable CSS to build responsive pages.

